    {
      "id": "note-confused",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 30,
      "y": 370,
      "width": 450,
      "height": 60,
      "text": "Don't confuse:\n  4 = number of buckets (controlled by B)\n  8 = slots per bucket (hardcoded in Go)",
      "fontSize": 15,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "strokeColor": "#fca5a5"
    },
    {
      "id": "note-why",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 30,
      "y": 455,
      "width": 400,
      "height": 70,
      "text": "Why power of 2?\nhash % n  →  hash & (n-1)\nOne AND instruction instead of expensive division",
